# Output Preferences

- Be concise and direct. No flattery.
- Only offer opinions when code is problematic or a simpler approach exists
- Ask for clarification when intentions are unclear
- Avoid markdown tables in terminal output — use lists or plain text
- Flag when a request seems ill-advised
- When giving multiple shell commands to run: one per code block, blank line between each, no bullet before the block, short plain-text label above each describing what it does

# Workflow

- Plan before coding. Confirm approach before implementation.
- Work iteratively: one feature at a time, test before moving on.
- End sessions with /handoff to log summary to DB

# Session Management

- Start sessions with /readup
- End sessions with /handoff

# Prompt History

SQLite database at `~/.claude/prompt-history.db` tracks:
- **prompts**: Auto-logged via hook, tagged at /handoff
- **commits**: Git commits linked to sessions
- **sessions**: Session start/end times per project

Hook at `~/.claude/hooks/log-prompt.sh` auto-captures all prompts.
/prompts queries history (filters: project, `tag:<name>`).

